  "name": "Channel Divinity: Turn Undead",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-creature-skeleton.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As an <strong>action</strong>, you present your holy symbol and speak a prayer censuring the undead.</p>\n<p>Each undead that can see or hear you within 30 feet of you must make a <strong>Wisdom saving throw</strong>. If the creature fails its saving throw, it is turned for 1 minute or until it takes any damage.</p>\n<p>A turned creature must spend its turns trying to move as far away from you as it can, and it can't willingly move to a space within 30 feet of you. It also can't take reactions.</p>\n<p>For its action, it can use only the <strong>Dash </strong>action or try to escape from an effect that prevents it from moving. If there's nowhere to move, the creature can use the <strong>Dodge </strong>action.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: When you add this feature to your character, set Resource Consumption to Item Uses: Channel Divinity.</em></p>\n</section>",
